transcript.text: Hello, thank you for joining us today.
I'm thrilled to introduce you to the preview image setting feature in our latest version of On Print Shop.
In the previous version, the preview image setting was product based, which posed a challenge.
When a product had multiple sizes, the admin had to set a common DPI for all sizes within that product.
However, in this new version, we have made a significant improvement by moving the preview image set from the product level to the studio level.
We have introduced A dedicated page in the Studio settings where the admin can conveniently set the preview image DPI based on the size.
This setting will be applicable to all products of that size, providing a more flexible and efficient approach.
Here, you can update the DPI based on the size.
You can create a different range of sizes and set the sizes.
Also, you can set the minimum and maximum dimensions in pixel.
Let's see how it works.
First, go to the Products Designer option.
Here your width and height will multiply with the DPI and show the quality of the image in the front end.
For example, in this product, the width is 3.75 and the height is 2.22.
Multiplying these values by our DPI setting of 170, we get a total DPI of 637 for the width and 377 for the height.
Furthermore, our system provides automatic recalculation of values to ensure they meet the specified minimum and maximum requirements.
If, for instance, the minimum value is set at 400 and the calculated height falls below the threshold, the system will adjust the height accordingly.
In this case, first the DPI will be recalculated to 180, resulting in a height of 400.
Now let's check it in the front end.
Click on the thumbnail and here you can open this image in a new tab.
When you hover over the tab, you can see the DPI values and that's it.
With our new preview DPI settings feature, you have more control and flexibility over the image quality and on print shop.
Thank you for watching.
